AuthenticationCode1.description: An authentication code emitted by the device. The format for this parameter is a sequence of six digits.

AuthenticationCode2.description: A subsequent authentication code emitted by the device. The format for this parameter is a sequence of six digits.

SerialNumber.description: Serial number that uniquely identifies the MFA device. This parameter allows (per its regex pattern) a string of characters consisting of upper and lowercase alphanumeric characters with no spaces. You can also include any of the following characters: =,.@-

UserName.description: The name of the user whose MFA device you want to resynchronize. This parameter allows (per its regex pattern) a string of characters consisting of upper and lowercase alphanumeric characters with no spaces. You can also include any of the following characters: =,.@-
